NFL TEAM SEASON RECAP 🧵: 𝗡𝗘, 𝗡𝗬𝗝, 𝗖𝗟𝗘, 𝗣𝗜𝗧

Carrying over my season summaries to the NFL for those teams now on holidays 🌴☀️. Starting with the AFC East/North and will post others over the coming days.

#nflverse

𝗡𝗘:

1/ https://t.co/7ljN7sAzdf

NFL TEAM SEASON RECAP 🧵: 𝗛𝗢𝗨, 𝗜𝗡𝗗, 𝗧𝗘𝗡, 𝗗𝗘𝗡, 𝗟𝗩

Today is AFC South/West, so likely some ugly reading for these teams. 🙈

#nflverse

𝗛𝗢𝗨:

1/ https://t.co/HsAUFSipIw

Day 75: Used a #SQL query to get the biggest blowouts by season from 1999-2022, data courtesy of #nflverse

Unsurprisingly, home teams are responsible for the biggest blowouts

The largest one in the last 23 yrs was in 2009 when the Pats beat the Titans 59-0

#100DaysOfCode https://t.co/8dkFWj8xDN

Obviously the AFC matchups are now known:

(7) MIA @ (2) BUF
(6) BAL @ (3) CIN
(5) LAC @ (4) JAX

(1) KC (bye)

I'm not going to put the games on https://t.co/cLipOV1bnf or in the #nflverse games data until we have all the games and know the scheduled dates/times.

KC locked up a 1 seed with their dominating win over the LV. Here's the pillboxes for KC offense. KC starters needed to come out a couple drives before they did. Is Andy trying to make playoff opponents forget about JuJu? Toney's killing it in a limited role. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/YsZRSx1YjE

KC defense. Ummm...where's Josh Williams? Did he miss the game? Harris took his traditional 3rd drive of the game from Gay. DL Williams still getting solid run. Oddly, Chenal didn't get any snaps in garbage time. I know passing downs aren't his role, but still.

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/SxuoFouOk1

Here's LV's charts, for the absolute degenerates who need to see them. Lotta runs early. Lotta passes late. Nate Hobbs either got injured or was replaced. It's not like they've got good DB's, so probs an injury. Hope he's alright. I didn't get to see the game. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/fLfhFXJOlV

The first 18 picks in the draft are now set.

Here is how the draft order would have changed if each team would have flipped their Week 18 result.

Simulation: @nflseedR #nflverse https://t.co/xTrlfYMtRh

FG % Over Expected vs Average FG Distance
#nflverse https://t.co/8r1bZQ9TOL

According to @ben_bot_baldwin,
Houston Texans had a 0,6% chance of converting 4&12 (20%), 4&20 (7%) and 2PAT (43%) all in this game!

#nflverse https://t.co/aorBaneboB

Here's the final 2022 NFL Regular season Time to Throw for each QB!

What's more impressive?
- Brady recorded the fastest time of his career this season! (W8 - 2.00s - #8 since 2016) 
- P.J.Walker recorder the fastest time overall since 2016! (W6 - 1.82s - #1)

#nflverse #ggplot2 https://t.co/ARcnshK67T

Trevor Lawrence had the worst 1st half of his career yesterday... But after a brilliant 2nd half by the Jaguars, he's now going to play on Divisional Round!

#nflverse #RStats #DUUUVAL https://t.co/lAP4DbAPK6
